+ ingress-nginx
    kubectl apply -f ...yaml
+ add env to kucernetes
    kubectl create secret generic jwt-secret --from-literal=JWT_KEY=asdf


+ SSR -> get service name

[1] kubectl get namespace
[2] kubectl get services -n <NGINX NAMESPACE>
baseURL:
        "http://[1].[2].svc.cluster.local",

+ npm package creation and use
    • npmjs.org -> register and create organization
    • package.json -> package name and version !!!
    • create git repo (git init; git add .; git commit -m "initial")
    • npm publish --access public 
        - if not logged in: npm login
    • because of npmjs uses js files: 
        tsc --init
        npm install typescript del-cli --save-dev
        // !!!  TO PACKAGE.JSON 
            "main": "./build/index.js", // entry point
            "types": "./build/index.d.ts", // type definition
            "files": [
                "build/**/*"
            ],
            "scripts": {
                "clean": "del ./build/*",
                "build": "npm run clean && tsc",
                "pub": "git add . && git commit -m \"Updates\" && npm version patch && npm run build && npm publish" // commit to git and publish to npm
            },
        // !!!

